subproject.description:
The project Support to Civil Society Development is collaboration between United Nations Development Program (UNDP) and the Australian Agency for International Development (AusAID).

The main objectives are:
1.	To sustain and expand the space created through democratic reforms for civil society to flourish. 
2.	To build capacities of civil society actors and empower civil society to effectively lobby for issues, particularly in the areas of human rights, democratic governance, gender equality and youth development
subproject.title: Support to Civil Society Dev't
